notes: The LLM provided no findings at all. It did not identify the target vulnerability in createLockedCampaign(), which involves an arbitrary external call to a user-provided tokenLocker address. This is a critical access_control vulnerability that was exploited in the real-world Hedgey Finance incident for $44.7M. The contract makes an unchecked call to tokenLocker.createTokenLock() without verifying the address, allowing attackers to steal tokens from approved users.
